-- Credit Suisse Hires Taketo Yamate From UBS to Cover Japanese Retailers
-- Eijiro Ueno
-- 2010-07-26T21:01:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/credit-suisse-hires-taketo-yamate-from-ubs-to-cover-japanese-retailers.html

          
          
             Credit Suisse Group AG ,
Switzerland’s second-biggest bank, hired  Taketo Yamate  from UBS
AG today to cover Japanese retailers.  
 Yamate, 33, will cover companies including  Fast Retailing
Co. ,  Kunihiko Shiohara , Credit Suisse’s Tokyo-based equity
research director, said. The bank’s Japanese equity research
department has almost 60 staff.  
 Yamate was ranked second among 13 analysts covering the
retail sector by the Nikkei Veritas newspaper this year. He will
also work with  Yoshiyasu Okihara , who covers food and tobacco
makers, to research consumer trends in Japan.  
